President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Patrick S. Moon as Ambassador to Bosnia and Herzegovina and Christopher W. Murray as Ambassador to the Republic of the Congo. Moon is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as Principal Deputy Assistant Secretary in the Bureau of South and Central Asian Affairs. Murray is also a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as Deputy Chief of Mission at the U.S. Mission to the European Union in Brussels. In addition to these nominations, President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Milford Wayne Donaldson as Chair of the Advisory Council on Historic Preservation. Donaldson currently serves as the State Historic Preservation Officer for California.